==Korean==
===Verb===
'''두다''' (du-da)
# To [[put]], cf. the archaic meaning of English [[do]] and German [[tun]]   
# To [[leave]] (behind), let there be
# To [[keep]] (from), [[preserve]]
# To [[have]] (in mind)
# To [[set up]] 

====Derived terms====
* [[놓다|놓아]]두다 (nohA-) To [[leave]] something [[laid]]
* [[잡다|잡아]]두다 (jabA-) To [[keep]] someone [[capture]]d

====See also==== 
* [[놓다]] (noh-da, not-ta) To [[lay]] 

